Version 2.9:
- [+] 20 Nov 2008, Vgv - Improvement (0056265): Sending of phone numbers of non-US customers to PayPal has been improved. 
- [+] 20 Jul 2009, Isden - Improvement (0074696): IPN configuration instruction is corrected.
- [!] 20 Nov 2009, Isden - Bug (0082593): Incompatibility with the latest ionCube and PHP versions is fixed.

Version 2.8:
- [!] 30 Jun 2008, Jasper - Bug (0030826): It was not taken into account that HTTPS could be switched on for checkout in the admin zone. That is why security warnings were displayed when the customer was returned to cart from PayPal. 
- [!] 09 Jun 2008, Jasper - Bug (0043875): The 'Express checkout' button was displayed to anonymous customers even when the corresponding payment method was disabled. Fixed.
- [+] 31 Mar 2008, Alien - Improvement (0037929): Equal duplicate transactions are not considered errors any more.
- [!] 01 Feb 2008, Alien - Bug (0034931): During module installation the file cart.html used in checkout desk mode was not patched, that is why some modules did not work. Fixed.
- [!] 29 Oct 2007, Alien - Bug (0028569): If a customer canceled the checkout after having been redirected to PayPal and was returned to the store's checkout page, clicking 'Submit order' once again lead to cart clearing instead of redirection to PayPal. Fixed. 

Version 2.7:
- [!] 26 Mar 2007, Sheriff - Bug (0018255): Phone numbers fields were filled incorrectly on the checkout step with the Website Payments Standard method. Fixed.

Version 2.6:
- [+] 28 Dec 2006, Sheriff - Improvement (0011464): PayPal response (from Website Payments Standard method)  verification procedure was improved.
- [+] 04 Dec 2006, Sheriff - Improvement (0006009): An ability to send shipping address details in the "Website Payments Pro" mode was added.

Version 2.5:
- [+] 09 Nov 2006, Sheriff - Improvement (0012936): An ability to set up "Service URL" parameter in the settings of "Standard" method was added.
- [+] 01 Nov 2006, Sheriff - Improvement (0012674): State verification procedure was changed to handle non-US states.
- [+] 19 Oct 2006, Sheriff - Improvement (0005338): Small PHP-code optimizing was made to neutralize customers' mistakes in the case-sensitive fields.
- [+] 18 Oct 2006, Sheriff - Improvement (0009779): Now it is possible to see a detailed error message in the customer zone.

Version 2.4:
- [!] 28 Sep 2006, Sheriff - Bug (0011464): When the successful transaction was received, the fields "Error" and "Description" in the order details were not cleared. Fixed.
- [+] 31 Jul 2006, Osipov - Improvement (0004839): The "Instant Payment Notification Preferences" note have been added to the module's configuration page.

Version 2.3:
- [!] 14 Jul 2006, Sheriff - Bug (0008123): When a customer used e-checks as a payment method, the status of order was not set correctly. Fixed.
- [+] 14 Jul 2006, Sheriff - Improvement (0007494): The 'State' field is now required to be accurately designated for UK and Australia. 
- [!] 25 May 2006, Sheriff - Bug (0005372): State was not being transmitted to PayPal correctly. Fixed.
- [!] 03 Mar 2006, Osipov - Bug(0006031): When PayPal was enabled, and one activated PayPalPro, all disabled modules were spontaneously activated.
- [!] 17 Feb 2006, Sheriff - Bug (0005915): Express checkout method - when HTTPS was turned on in the customer zone, URLs passed to PayPal were incorrect (some special characters were not converted to HTML entities). Fixed.

Version 2.2: 
- [!] 27 Jan 2006, Asd - Bug (0005664): Standard method - country code was not being transmitted to PayPal. Fixed.
- [!] 27 Jan 2006, Asd - Bug (0005643): Paying with eChecks caused 'duplicate transaction error' on PayPal side. Fixed.
- [!] 06 Jan 2006, Asd - Bug (0005461): Discover Card Code was being transmitted incorrectly. Fixed.
- [!] 14 Dec 2005, Asd - Bug (0004843): State was not being transmitted to PayPal. Fixed.
- [!] 03 Oct 2005, Asd - Bug (0004335): Express checkout method - LiteCommerce was crashing if the customer's PayPal login e-mail was matching LiteCommerce profile e-mail. Fixed.

Version 2.1:
- [!] 18 Aug 2005, Asd - Bug: DirectPayment didn't change order status because order was not updated after payment had been made.
- [+] 17 Aug 2005, Asd - Improvement: Now the shipping info is sent to PayPal side instead of the billing info (makes it easier to create new PayPal accounts). Fixed.



